The man was arrested on Saturday for impersonating North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo and threatening to bomb the premier's home. JOHANNESBURG A 25-year-old man is expected to appear in the Mmabatho Magistrates Court on Wednesday on charges of conspiracy to commit murder and intimidation.He was arrested by the Hawks on Christmas Eve in the Northern Cape for allegedly impersonating the North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo in a bid to solicit money from high profile leaders.The office of the premier has warned the public of the scam after receiving several calls from high profile politicians including a Western Cape-based member of Parliament.It is alleged that the man also threatened to bomb the premier s home when his extortion attempts were unsuccessful.Hawks spokesperson Tlangelani Rikhotso says that while their investigations continue, charges of fraud against the suspect could be added on the initial charges. The suspect allegedly tried to solicit money from different people. Claiming to be the North West premier and secondly claiming to be the son of the Botswana president. When he was failing to get this money, he allegedly then threatened to bomb the premiers house, so that s where these charges come from. (Edited by Neo Koza)